    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <head>No. 381.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Schuyler</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-05-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 175, of the 23d ultimo,
                            covering a printed document relative to the International Statistical
                            Congress to be held at St. Petersburg in August next, has been received.
                            In reply, I have to state that Mr. Edward Young, Chief of the Bureau of
                            Statistics in the Treasury Department, has been appointed a delegate to
                            represent, the United States in said congress.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
